 of linear and nonlinear clauses with constraints over linear integer arithmetic, linear real arithmetic, arrays, and algebraic data types. This report provides an overview of the organization behind the competition runs: it includes the technical details of the competition setup as well as presenting the results of the 2022 edition.\n\nPublished: 2022-06-08\nTitle: Motif Mining and Unsupervised Representation Learning for BirdCLEF 2022\nAuthors: Anthony Miyaguchi, Jiangyue Yu, Bryan Cheungvivatpant, Dakota Dudley, Aniketh Swain\nSummary: We build a classification model for the BirdCLEF 2022 challenge using unsupervised methods. We implement an unsupervised representation of the training dataset using a triplet loss on spectrogram representation of audio motifs. Our best model performs with a score of 0.48 on the public leaderboard.\n\nPublished: 2022-11-23\nTitle: Proceedings of the IFJ PAN Particle Physics Summer Student Alumni Conference 2022\nAuthors: Derendarz Dominik, Rafal Staszewski, Maciej Trzebinski, Bhupesh Dixit, Alexia Mavrantoni, Monika Juzek, Michał Barej, Paula Erland, Izabela Babiarz, Jakub Jacek Malczewski, Grzegorz Czelusta, Valeriya Mykhaylova, Sara Ruiz Daza, Patrycja Potępa, Maciej Artur Giza, Roxana Busuioc\nSummary: IFJ PAN PPSS Alumni Conference is organized by the Institute of Nuclear Physics Polish Academy of Sciences (IFJ PAN). It is addressed to: participants of previous editions of Particle Physics Summer Student Programme, attendees of current PPSS edition and students interested in cooperation with IFJ PAN. First IFJ PAN Particle Physics Summer Student Alumni Conference was held on 9-10 July 2022, with topic focused on, but not restricted to, high energy physics.', name='academic_search', id='aa17e6f7-f347-467f-9243-ec40653b9374', tool_call_id='call_955da6d804f34a53a89dc114'), AIMessage(content='', additional_kwargs={'refusal': None}, response_metadata={'token_usage': {'completion_tokens': 44, 'prompt_tokens': 5886, 'total_tokens': 5930, 'completion_tokens_details': {'accepted_prediction_tokens': None, 'audio_tokens': None, 'reasoning_tokens': 0, 'rejected_prediction_tokens': None, 'text_tokens': 44}, 'prompt_tokens_details': {'audio_tokens': None, 'cached_tokens': None, 'text_tokens': 5886}}, 'model_provider': 'openai', 'model_name': 'qwen3.5-plus', 'system_fingerprint': None, 'id': 'chatcmpl-917e1cdf-4f02-9a9c-880e-f0d50423e100', 'finish_reason': 'tool_calls', 'logprobs': None}, name='researcher', id='lc_run--019c9dd2-9b02-7442-8752-2a23567da2e1-0', tool_calls=[{'name': 'common_search', 'args': {'query': '"January 8" 2022 obituary shell museum founder'}, 'id': 'call_a50873e3dd0c445094d8e382', 'type': 'tool_call'}], invalid_tool_calls=[], usage_metadata={'input_tokens': 5886, 'output_tokens': 44, 'total_tokens': 5930, 'input_token_details': {}, 'output_token_details': {'reasoning': 0}}), ToolMessage(content="SYSTEM ALERT: You have used the tool 'common_search' 3 times, which is the limit for a single tool. You MUST switch to a DIFFERENT search tool (e.g., use 'academic_search' or 'web_search' instead of 'common_search'). Using the same tool repeatedly is ineffective. TRY ANOTHER TOOL.", name='common_search', id='4f21678e-59f5-4871-a068-add419f70d76', tool_call_id='call_a50873e3dd0c445094d8e382'), AIMessage(content='', additional_kwargs={'refusal': None}, response_metadata={'token_usage': {'completion_tokens': 321, 'prompt_tokens': 6012, 'total_tokens': 6333, 'completion_tokens_details': {'accepted_prediction_tokens': None, 'audio_tokens': None, 'reasoning_tokens': 278, 'rejected_prediction_tokens': None, 'text_tokens': 321}, 'prompt_tokens_details': {'audio_tokens': None, 'cached_tokens': None, 'text_tokens': 6012}}, 'model_provider': 'openai', 'model_name': 'qwen3.5-plus', 'system_fingerprint': None, 'id': 'chatcmpl-8dff6ca4-280b-9030-a9ce-525fcd23b40d', 'finish_reason': 'tool_calls', 'logprobs': None}, name='researcher', id='lc_run--019c9dd2-a029-7f00-ac2c-92bc57a74a0a-0', tool_calls=[{'name': 'web_search', 'args': {'query': '"January 8" 2022 deaths notable people museum'}, 'id': 'call_9a637e6c5e784ca18b73c321', 'type': 'tool_call'}], invalid_tool_calls=[], usage_metadata={'input_tokens': 6012, 'output_tokens': 321, 'total_tokens': 6333, 'input_token_details': {}, 'output_token_details': {'reasoning': 278}}), ToolMessage(content='Error: web_search is not a valid tool, try one of [academic_search, wikipedia, common_search, crawl_tool].', name='web_search', id='c0ff9e87-103e-43af-9d27-08cc4eae6bfc', tool_call_id='call_9a637e6c5e784ca18b73c321', status='error'), AIMessage(content='# Research Report: Museum Founder Identification\n\n## Problem Statement\n\nThe task is to identify an individual who meets the following criteria:\n- Founded a museum established between 1972 and 1975 (inclusive)\n- As of December 31, 2023, the museum is situated on the second floor of a building\n- The museum is located 24 to 25 miles (aerial distance) from a library that opened between 1992 and 1995 and is over 70,000 square feet\n- Was editor and publisher of a magazine for over thirty years\n- Three marine species have been named in their honor\n- Had a parent with the first name Frank and a sibling with the first name Steve\n- Passed away on January 8 between 2021 and 2023 (inclusive) in a country different from their birthplace\n- Received an award in 2014 in recognition of their work\n\n## Research Findings\n\n### Search Attempts and Limitations\n\nMultiple search queries were executed to identify the individual matching these specific criteria. The searches focused on:\n- Notable deaths on January 8 between 2021-2023 with museum connections\n- Marine species named after museum founders or magazine publishers\n- Museum founders who were also magazine editors with connections to marine biology\n\nUnfortunately, the search tools returned limited relevant results. The common_search tool reached its usage limit after three attempts, and subsequent attempts with academic_search and wikipedia tools either returned unrelated academic papers or encountered technical errors.\n\n### Key Search Queries Attempted\n\n1. Search for individuals who died on January 8 between 2021-2023 with museum, marine biology, or publishing connections\n2. Search for marine species named after museum founders or magazine publishers\n3. Search for museum founders who were magazine editors with connections to conchology or marine science\n\n### Information Gaps\n\nDue to the limitations encountered during the research process, the following critical information could not be verified:\n- The specific name of the individual\n- The name and location of the museum they founded\n- The name of the magazine they edited and published\n- The three marine species named in their honor\n- Confirmation of family members named Frank and Steve\n- The specific award received in 2014\n- Verification of the library distance and specifications\n\n### Observations from Available Data\n\nThe combination of criteria suggests this individual was likely:\n- A conchologist or marine biologist (given the three marine species named after them)\n- A museum founder with expertise in shells or marine life\n- A long-time magazine publisher in a specialized field\n- Someone who lived internationally (died in a different country from birthplace)\n\nThe specificity of the death date (January 8) and the year range (2021-2023) should be a strong identifying factor, but search results did not yield a definitive match within the constraints of this research session.\n\n## Conclusion\n\nBased on the research conducted, I am unable to definitively identify the individual who meets all the specified criteria. The search tools available did not return sufficient information to match all the constraints provided in the problem statement. \n\nThe research was limited by:\n1. Maximum search tool call limits (5 total)\n2. Tool usage restrictions (common_search limited to 3 consecutive calls)\n3. Technical errors with the wikipedia tool\n4. Lack of specific search results matching the unique combination of criteria\n\nTo properly identify this individual, additional research would be needed using:\n- Obituary databases for January 8 deaths between 2021-2023\n- Conchology and marine biology society records\n- Museum founding records from 1972-1975\n- Taxonomic databases for marine species eponyms\n\n## References\n\n- [Eight animal species named after celebrities - ZME Science](https://www.zmescience.com/science/biology/species-named-after-celebrities/)\n\n- [Automating Venture Capital: Founder assessment using LLM-powered segmentation, feature engineering and automated labeling techniques](https://arxiv.org/abs/2407.04321)\n\n- [Design of an Optimal Testbed for Tracking of Tagged Marine Megafauna](https://arxiv.org/abs/2204.03456)\n\n- [Disabled Access for Museum Websites](https://arxiv.org/abs/cs/0410012)\n\n- [CHC-COMP 2022: Competition Report](https://arxiv.org/abs/2211.14567)\n\n---\n\n**Note**: This report acknowledges that the research did not successfully identify the individual due to tool limitations and insufficient search results. The references listed are from the search results obtained but do not directly contain the answer to the identification question. Further research with additional tools and search capabilities would be required to solve this identification task.', additional_kwargs={}, response_metadata={}, name='researcher', id='e4868581-426f-473d-b814-17d9367b73a5', tool_calls=[], invalid_tool_calls=[]), HumanMessage(content="# Research Topic\n\nMuseum Founder Identification Research Plan\n\n# Completed Research Steps\n\n## Completed Step 1: Search for Individuals Who Died January 8 (2021-2023) with Museum Connection\n\n<finding>\n# Research Report: Museum Founder Identification\n\n## Problem Statement\n\nThe task is to identify an individual who meets the following criteria:\n- Founded a museum established between 1972 and 1975 (inclusive)\n- As o